time required: 45 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

In a small #pot, combine @pearl barley{3/4%cup}, 2 1/2 cups water (4 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cover. Cook until barley is tender and water has absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 6.

> TIP: If you end up with any excess water, simply pour it out. Alternatively, if water evaporates before barley is done, add a splash of water.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}, cut lengthwise into halves; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Pick leaves from @cilantro{1/4%ounce}; finely chop leaves.

Toss zucchini, bell pepper, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of cooking oil, ½ tsp @harissa powder{1%tbsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{} and @pepper{}. (Be sure to measure the harissa powder—we sent more! Use less if you prefer less heat.)

Roast on top rack until veggies are tender and browned, ~{15-18%minutes}. (For 4, divide between 2 baking sheets; roast on top and middle racks.)

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

In a small #bowl, combine @yogurt{4%tbsp} and a big pinch of lemon zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine cilantro, @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste (use 3 TBSP olive oil and ½ tsp garlic powder for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a small, dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Fluff barley with a #fork. Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, remaining garlic powder, a squeeze of lemon juice, and as much remaining lemon zest as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir half the veggies into pot with barley.

Divide barley between bowls; top with remaining veggies, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and almonds. Drizzle with yogurt and herb sauce. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges and remaining chili flakes on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise; serve chicken atop bowls.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.